# Docs, diaries & decisions

The `docs/` tree is the project's memory. Read order and rules live in
`AGENTS.md` and the per-directory READMEs — follow them, don't restate them here.

- **Every doc has YAML front-matter.** `title`, `type`, `updated` plus
  type-specific fields; the `type` discriminator selects the schema. This is
  machine-checked by the AF-6 doc linter (`pnpm doc-lint`) against
  `node_modules/@agent-workflow/doc-linter/front-matter.schema.json` (field rules in
  `docs/specs/agent-workflow.md` §4). Dates are ISO (`YYYY-MM-DD`).
- **Diaries: knowledge, not a journal.** Record knowledge worth re-deriving —
  quirks, dead ends, non-obvious trade-offs, gotchas, and do-NOTs — not
  play-by-play. Source of truth: `docs/agent-diaries/README.md` (ADR-0008).
- **Decisions are ADRs — owner participates first.** Present options, wait for owner
  input, then record `Proposed` and implement if scoped. Only the owner sets
  `Accepted`. Process: `docs/adr/README.md`; always-on gate: `.cursor/rules/owner-participation.mdc`.
- **Link, don't duplicate** — one source of truth per fact, and relative links
  must resolve (the linter checks this).
- **Feature specs** scope one backlog item per session (`docs/specs/features/`).
  Workflow and acceptance-criteria patterns: `docs/specs/features/README.md` (AF-8).
- **Keep TODO and backlog in sync.** Copy/break down backlog items into
  `docs/TODO.md`; mark a backlog item `completed` only when its TODO work closes
  it. The backlog is durable — never delete from it.
- **Incidents: report before fix.** User-reported bugs → run
  `pnpm gen:create-incident-report` first (`docs/incident-reports/`, skill
  `create-incident-report`). Postmortem only after fix and with user permission
  (`pnpm gen:create-postmortem`, skill `create-postmortem`).
